(552, 1, 31, 'Use 375,000 images from the Met however you want, for free', 'https://www.engadget.com/2017/02/09/use-375-000-images-from-the-met-however-you-want-for-free/', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://s.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/midas/5ac3f38b1c5fb7ba3b504404bc38426f/204915108/met-public-domain-2017-02-09-03-ed.jpg', 'If you want to use images of paintings from the Metropolitan Museum of Art, like Woman with a Parrot by Gustave Courbet (above), you no longer have to worry about rights. All of the Met\'s approximately 375,000 public-domain artwork images are now available for free, unrestricted use. The new \"Open Access\" policy, based on Creative Commons Zero (CC0), means bloggers, schools and businesses alike can use them without even the need for attribution.', 0, NULL, NULL, 1),
(553, 1, 52, 'New nanotech to detect cancer early', 'https://www.ted.com/talks/joshua_smith_new_nanotech_to_catch_cancer_early', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://pi.tedcdn.com/r/pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/43936e67c46e89faf0c1f486095bcafa38c1aab6_2880x1620.jpg?c=1050%2C550', 'What if every home had an early-warning cancer detection system? Researcher Joshua Smith is developing a nanobiotechnology &quot;cancer alarm&quot; that scans for traces of disease in the form of special biomarkers called exosomes. In this forward-thinking talk, he shares his dream for how we might revolutionize cancer detection and, ultimately, save lives.', 0, NULL, NULL, 1),
(554, 1, 25, 'How to Create a Surreal, Emotional Scene With Adobe Photoshop', 'https://design.tutsplus.com/tutorials/create-a-surreal-emotional-scene-with-photoshop--cms-27986', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://cms-assets.tutsplus.com/uploads/users/723/posts/27986/final_image/bird-final.jpg', 'This site was designed for modern browsers and tested with Internet Explorer version 10 and later.', 0, NULL, NULL, 1),
(555, 1, 57, 'This Image Teaches You What Breast Cancer Can Look Like', 'http://vitals.lifehacker.com/learn-what-breast-cancer-can-look-like-with-this-cute-i-1791179098', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/s--CRg_ziS2--/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/amd81hl0yr54dn8yoyif.png', 'You’ve probably heard that you should see a doctor if you notice any changes in your breasts, since lumps and other anomalies can be signs of breast cancer. But do you even know what changes you’re looking for? Let these lemons explain.', 0, NULL, NULL, 1),
